      • provideExecutorService

        protected ExecutorService provideExecutorService()
        Description copied from class: TelegramBot
        Instantiates and returns an ExecutorService. By default, Executors.newCachedThreadPool() is used. This method can safely be overridden to adjust this behaviour. This method can safely be overridden to return null, but if you decide to do so, TelegramBot.notifyNewMessages(List) must be overridden to avoid a NPE.
        Overrides:
        provideExecutorService in class TelegramBot
        Returns:
        An instantiated ExecutorService

      • shouldSendAsync

        protected boolean shouldSendAsync()
        Description copied from class: TelegramBot
        Returns whether the bot should asynchronously send requests. By default, this method returns true. It can be overridden adjust this behaviour.
        Overrides:
        shouldSendAsync in class TelegramBot
        Returns:

      • notifyNewMessages

        protected void notifyNewMessages(List<Message> messages)
        Description copied from class: TelegramBot
        This method is called by this class to process all new Messages asynchronously. It must be overridden if TelegramBot.provideExecutorService() is overridden to return null, otherwise a NullPointerException may be thrown.
        Overrides:
